@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-4">

    <h2 class="mb-3">Welcome to LibraryManager</h2>

    <p>
        <strong>LibraryManager</strong> is a full‑stack library management system built with modern .NET technologies.
        It combines a secure backend API with a fast, interactive Blazor WebAssembly frontend to deliver a smooth and
        responsive user experience.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">Key Features</h4>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>ASP.NET Core Web API</strong> powering all backend operations</li>
        <li><strong>Entity Framework Core</strong> with code‑first migrations for database access</li>
        <li><strong>ASP.NET Identity</strong> for secure authentication and role‑based authorization</li>
        <li><strong>JWT authentication</strong> for Blazor WASM client communication</li>
        <li><strong>Borrowing system</strong> with real‑time availability updates</li>
        <li><strong>Borrow history tracking</strong> for users and administrators</li>
        <li><strong>Profile management</strong> with user details and borrowed books</li>
        <li><strong>Admin features</strong> for managing books, users, and library activity</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mt-3">
        This project demonstrates a complete, production‑ready architecture using modern .NET practices,
        clean API design, and a rich client‑side UI built with Blazor WebAssembly.
    </p>

</div>
